shortDescription: "There are no float literals"
shortCorrection: "An F or f suffix can turn a number into a float literal"
concepts:

Java does not provide a way to directly write numbers of type `float`.
Values of type `float` can only be created by casting,
e.g., `(float)3.14`.

frontmatter.shortCorrection: An F or f suffix can turn a number into a float literal
